MR);\n--- End Patch ---\n\nThis preserves the original behavior while adding a
safe handling path for null UO.\n\n5. Conclusion:\nThe crash stems from assuming
getUnderlyingObjectAggressive never returns null. By adding a null check in
addLocAccess() and conservatively classifying memory effects when UO is null, we
avoid the assertion and maintain correct, conservative attribute inference. This
fix prevents the abort in function-attrs on the provided reproducer and similar
IR patterns.",
